### 2.3 Distribution
- Distribution of the original or modified Software to third parties.
- Integration of the Software into other projects, subject to conditions.

## 3. Mandatory Obligations of Licensee

### 3.1 Attribution and Proprietary Notice
For every source file utilizing NEHONIX code, the Licensee MUST include the following comment at the top of the file:

```
/* * This code contains proprietary source code from NEHONIX * Copyright © 2025 NEHONIX - www.nehonix.com * Licensed under NEHONIX Open Source License (NOSL) v1.0 */
```

For languages without multi-line comments, adapt to the appropriate format (# for Python, // for certain languages, etc.).

### 3.2 Documentation of Ownership
The Licensee MUST:
- Include the original LICENSE file in any distribution.
- Reference NEHONIX in the README file or main documentation with the following text:
  "This project uses code developed by NEHONIX (www.nehonix.com) under the NEHONIX Open Source License (NOSL) v1.0."
- Preserve all copyright and license notices present in the Software.

### 3.3 Contribution to Principal Project
Prior to using the code in another project, the Licensee MUST:
- Submit a Pull Request to the Principal Project for any significant modification or improvement.
- Allow reasonable time (30 days) for review by the NEHONIX team.
- This obligation does not apply to minor bug fixes or internal adaptations not distributed publicly.

### 3.4 Commercial and Marketing Use
For any commercial or marketing use of the Software, the Licensee MUST:
- Clearly display "Powered by NEHONIX" in:
  - Marketing materials (website, brochures, advertisements)
  - Product documentation
  - Commercial presentations
- Include the NEHONIX logo where visually appropriate (logo available upon request).
- Not suggest partnership or endorsement by NEHONIX without written authorization.

### 3.5 License Preservation
Any distribution of the Software, modified or not, MUST:
- Be conducted under this same License (NOSL v1.0).
- Include a complete copy of this License.
- Not impose additional restrictions on the rights granted herein.

